The paper deals with deep reinforcement learning and regularization techniques to improve the sparsity of the learned representations. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper investigates the performance of the agents in two different benchmark domains, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
